import os  # importing module to interact with OS in python  
os.system('pip install -r requirements.txt')     # Install the dependencies from requirement file    pip is a package manager for Python and it will handle dependency management by itself; this command tells your computer that we want installing all packages mentioned inside "requirements" into our current environment  Requirement might include something like numpy, pandas etc., python-dotenv to manage secret keys or any others dependencies.  
os.system('python -m pytest')     # running tests; it's using a command line tool for testing in Python called PyTest which is the most popular option among developers because of its simplicity and flexibility    It should point out if there are no test cases then you can proceed with deployment, otherwise please run your code first.
os.system('python setup.py bdist_wheel')     # packaging; it's a command-line tool provided by Python for creating source archive or distribution package which is compatible to PyPI   It will create an .egg/.whl file in the 'build'/ directory  this can be uploaded on our server and then installed using pip.